{
  "stem": "150.2",
  "chunk_idx": 17,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Why did Hitler let you survive if he wanted to kill all Jews?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, if he let you live, then you're a collaborator because you must have done something for them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then bad things happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I decided not to go back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I hitched a ride back to my displaced person camp in Landsberg.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I came back, and oh my god, everybody was really very nervous.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were not happy to see me at all because they thought the Russians would come looking for me, my name was on the list, and that it would be difficult for people.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was getting to be very unpleasant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then just as if by coincidence, all of a sudden, a whole bunch of military-- British military-- this was an American zone-- but British military trucks with a steering wheel on the wrong side rolled into the DP camp.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And all these British military trucks have a big star of David on the side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I thought, what is that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there is British soldiers, and it says Palestine with the Star of David.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was the British-- the Palestinian Brigade of the British army, the 30,000 volunteers that the British finally permitted to volunteer to fight with the Allies.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was, of course, also a division of the Arabs and the Muslims, but that was not with the British Army.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was the SS Muslim division with the mufti sitting in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So there was also the-- speaking of the Bosnian situation, there was the Bosnia Herzegovnia SS battalion who were so terrible in the Ukraine that the Germans had to pull them out because of the atrocities they committed against the peaceful population.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But that's another story.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyway, the British-- the Palestinian brigade was stationed in Italy.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
